## рҹ“қ CONVENCIONES DE CГ“DIGO

> **Nota:** Las convenciones detalladas de cГіdigo estГЎn disponibles en los skills de `.agents/`
> - Backend (Python/FastAPI): `systematic-debugging`, `error-handling-patterns`, `supabase-postgres-best-practices`
> - Frontend (React Native/Expo): `vercel-react-best-practices`, `vercel-composition-patterns`, `react-native-best-practices`, `building-native-ui`

### Python (Backend)

```python
# вң… Correcto
from app.schemas.product import ProductResponse
from app.services.product_service import get_products

async def list_products(db: AsyncSession) -> list[ProductResponse]:
    """Docstring conciso explicando propГіsito."""
    products = await get_products(db)
    return [ProductResponse.model_validate(p) for p in products]

# вқҢ Incorrecto
def list_products(db):  # Sin async, sin tipos
    return db.query(Product).all()  # Query directo (debe estar en service)
```

**Reglas Python:**
- вң… Type hints obligatorios
- вң… Async/await para I/O (DB, HTTP)
- вң… Docstrings en funciones pГәblicas
- вң… snake_case para funciones y variables
- вқҢ No usar `print()` (usar logging)
- вқҢ No usar `Any` de typing

### TypeScript (Frontend)

```typescript
// вң… Correcto
interface Product {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  price: number;
}

export const fetchProducts = async (): Promise<Product[]> => {
  const response = await fetch(`${API_URL}/products`);
  if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch');
  return response.json();
};

// вқҢ Incorrecto
export const fetchProducts = async (): Promise<any> => {  // No any
  return fetch('/products').then(r => r.json());  // URL hardcodeada
};
```

**Reglas TypeScript:**
- вң… Interfaces para objetos complejos
- вң… Types explГӯcitos (no `any`)
- вң… Async/await (no .then())
- вң… PascalCase para componentes e interfaces
- вң… camelCase para funciones y variables
- вқҢ No `var` (usar `const`/`let`)
- вқҢ No `require()` (usar `import`)

---

## рҹ”Қ DEBUGGING

> **Nota:** Para debugging sistemГЎtico, usa el skill `systematic-debugging` de .agents/skills/

### Logging

**Backend (Python):**
```python
import logging

logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)

# вң… Correcto
logger.info(f"Fetching products for user {user_id}")
logger.error(f"Database error: {str(e)}", exc_info=True)

# вқҢ Incorrecto
print(f"User token: {token}")  # No print, no tokens
```

**Frontend (React Native):**
```typescript
// вң… Correcto
console.log('ProductList rendered with', products.length, 'items');
console.error('Failed to fetch products:', error.message);

// вқҢ Incorrecto
console.log('User token:', token);  // No loguear tokens
alert('Error');  // Usar toast/notification UI
```

